      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of August 17 article in Circuits column on bicycle computers</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in Circuits on Aug. 17 about bicycle computers referred incorrectly to their means of measuring pedal rhythm, or cadence. Only rotations of the crank are tracked, by sensors; gear sizes do not have to be entered into the computer.</p>
      </block>
